  [1] " Left bragged to colleagues that some of [his] statements were espec=
ially effective at inducing retail investors to trade based on his recommen=
dations and said that it was like taking 'candy from a baby,'" says the SEC=
.


  [2] The Justice Department says: =E2=80=9CAs further alleged in the indic=
tment, in the leadup to publication of Citron=E2=80=99s commentary, Left es=
tablished long or short positions in the public company on which he was com=
menting in his trading accounts and prepared to quickly close those positio=
ns post-publication and take profits on the short-term price movement cause=
d by his commentary. Left allegedly used his advance knowledge and control =
over the timing of a market-moving event to build his positions using inexp=
ensive, short-dated options contracts that expired from the same day that h=
e published his commentary to within five days. Left also allegedly submitt=
ed limit orders, often prior to publication of his commentary, to close his=
 positions as soon as the company=E2=80=99s shares reached a certain price =
and at prices vastly different from the target prices that Left recommended=
 to the public.=E2=80=9D I mean! If you believe my arguments that closing o=
ut the position can be okay, then putting in limit orders in advance is als=
o fine. Kind of looks bad though.


  [3] It has some complaints: Citron and Left=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Clack of a =
reasonable basis in selecting target prices further demonstrates their lack=
 of belief in those prices,=E2=80=9D says the SEC. Also there=E2=80=99s a w=
eird story about a company called VUZI, where Left bought some stock and th=
en tweeted that he was *not short*: =E2=80=9C=E2=80=9CGetting emails about =
shorting $VUZI. NO WAY we would short this flyer. Small market cap with sto=
ry that is tied to 5G, $AMZN and $PLUG and Covid. There has to be easier pi=
ckings...still doing research. Risk/Reward easier on other high flyers.=E2=
=80=9D The stock went up. Then his associated did some due diligence and de=
cided =E2=80=9Cwe can=E2=80=99t have enough conviction in this being an act=
ual long,=E2=80=9D so they sold. The SEC thinks this is fraud but =E2=80=A6=
 I mean =E2=80=A6 it was all true, no?


