<div id=3D"footnote-1" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[1] " Left bragged to colleagues that some of =
[his] statements were especially effective at inducing retail investors to =
trade based on his recommendations and said that it was like taking 'candy =
from a baby,'" says the SEC.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-2" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[2] The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/36208872.193392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3Yvb3BhL3By=
L2FjdGl2aXN0LXNob3J0LXNlbGxlci1jaGFyZ2VkLTE2bS1zdG9jay1tYXJrZXQtbWFuaXB1bGF=
0aW9uLXNjaGVtZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC2b5f29a9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Justice Departme=
nt says</a>: =E2=80=9CAs further alleged in the indictment, in the leadup t=
o publication of Citron=E2=80=99s commentary, Left established long or shor=
t positions in the public company on which he was commenting in his trading=
 accounts and prepared to quickly close those positions post-publication an=
d take profits on the short-term price movement caused by his commentary. L=
eft allegedly used his advance knowledge and control over the timing of a m=
arket-moving event to build his positions using inexpensive, short-dated op=
tions contracts that expired from the same day that he published his commen=
tary to within five days. Left also allegedly submitted limit orders, often=
 prior to publication of his commentary, to close his positions as soon as =
the company=E2=80=99s shares reached a certain price and at prices vastly d=
ifferent from the target prices that Left recommended to the public.=E2=80=
=9D I mean! If you believe my arguments that closing out the position can b=
e okay, then putting in limit orders in advance is also fine. Kind of looks=
 bad though.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-3" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[3] It has some complaints: Citron and Left=E2=
=80=99s =E2=80=9Clack of a reasonable basis in selecting target prices furt=
her demonstrates their lack of belief in those prices,=E2=80=9D says the SE=
C. Also there=E2=80=99s a weird story about a company called VUZI, where Le=
ft bought some stock and then tweeted that he was *not short*: =E2=80=9C=E2=
=80=9CGetting emails about shorting $VUZI. NO WAY we would short this flyer=
. Small market cap with story that is tied to 5G, $AMZN and $PLUG and Covid=
. There has to be easier pickings...still doing research. Risk/Reward easie=
r on other high flyers.=E2=80=9D The stock went up. Then his associated did=
 some due diligence and decided =E2=80=9Cwe can=E2=80=99t have enough convi=
ction in this being an actual long,=E2=80=9D so they sold. The SEC thinks t=
his is fraud but =E2=80=A6 I mean =E2=80=A6 it was all true, no?</p>
</div>
</td>
